Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Combine cream, mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, Asiago cheese, salt, and pepper together in a bowl. Scoop 1 cup of cheese mixture in bottom of a baking dish. Layer cauliflower into baking dish; cover with remaining cheese mixture. Bake in preheated oven until cauliflower is easily pierced with a fork, 20 to 30 minutes.